  "text": "My favorite spring cocktails and mocktails are filled with aperol spritzes, kombucha smashes, grapefruit margaritas and more. Perfect way to wind down just as the weather gets warm and springy. It’s officially spring! I mean, spring is definitely in the air over here. We get one small tastes of it and I am here for all the warm weather beverages. There is just nothing like when the weather first warms up and drags you out of the winter gloom. Since things are ever-so-slighty looking up, there is a great reason to enjoy a cocktail (or mocktail) on the patio in the lovely spring weather. The days are longer, spring is so close we can taste it and it’s the perfect reason to make a fun drink. I’m very partial to a spritz these days or even a smash with some fresh fruit. Something very light and refreshing and simple. There are a few of my favorite mocktails sprinkled in here, along with some of the best spring cocktails I’ve made over the years. They are so delish! Which one is calling your name? 18 Spring Cocktails and Mocktails Mimosa Punch Bubbly Jam Margaritas Pink Grapefruit Margaritas with Chili Salt Cucumber Mint Margaritas Lemon Sorbet Prosecco Floats Rosé Aperol Spritz Lavender Blueberry Vodka Soda Palomas with Salty Chili Sugar Blood Orange Tequila Fizz Strawberry Citrus Punch Blood Orange Cooler Kombucha Sangria Triple Citrus Kombucha Fizz Grapefruit Daiquiris Frozen Mimosas Clementine Cream Sodas Hummingbird Mimosas Clementine Vodka Sodas",
